%h2 Boo Adventure
%p
  To design the programming language part of the project, I'm using an existing language called Boo. It's open source, pre-1.0, and under active development, so things are fairly volatile.
  I ran into an issue in the latest official release that probably would've prevented me from doing some of the cooler language features I was planning. I spent a day developing a workaround,
  but it still wasn't quite what I needed. I asked the Boo mailing list, and the main Boo developer replied in a few hours with a new version that does exactly what I wanted.
%p
  That was great, but it's not in an official release yet, so that also meant that I had to update my project to target the latest Boo. Changing dependencies is always a pain, and targeting
  bleeding-edge Boo also introduces risk into my project, so I have mixed feelings, but I don't really have a choice until an official release comes out.

